Location: In-person (111 Cummington Mall - Room 152)
SCHOOL/COLLEGE (STUDENTS) OR BUSINESS NAME (EXTERNAL PARTNERS): Boston University/CAS
What is your predicted graduation year? (Question applies to students only): Spring 2020
How did you hear about us?: Current Student
If "other" please state the nature of referral:
Please describe what you hope to receive from office hours?: An opportunity to not only learn new techniques in implementing the functionality of project ideas but also to contribute something for others to use.
Do you have a venture in mind? (Students Only): Maybe
If "yes" or "maybe" please describe your venture: I wish to create a platform for students to post times that they are free throughout the semester as well as for student groups/ organizations to post schedules of their own events/meetings for students to view or learn about. It is not to challenge already existing platforms such as Eventbrite or other ticketing platforms but to provide notice of meetings that occur across campus.
What problem are you seeking to solve with your venture?: An issue that continues to persist throughout BU is how low attendance is for many student organizations as well as the fact that many students often voice a complaint of not finding a group that they can be a part of. Students often have some free time to spend but do not know how to spend it and student clubs/organizations that are growing are often overlooked by larger groups. My aim is to have something that can notify people clubs or organizations that interest students so that problems on both ends can be addressed.
How far along is your venture?: I am currently trying to build the foundation of both students and organizations being able to submit their schedules for events. My plan is to add further functionalities such as event/meeting types, expanding/adding specifications to schedules (perhaps monthly instead of weekly) and eventually web functionality.
Appointment Type : General Consultation
